<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="675" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">
                        <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss> files, lot 59 D 237, “Membership”</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by an <gloss type="from">Adviser of the United States Delegation</gloss> to the General
                            Assembly</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Key</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-10-08">October 8,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <list type="subject">
                        <item>Subject:</item>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Membership</item>
                    </list>
                    <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SARASINP1">Sarasin</persName> (Thailand)
                        informed me that his delegation would vote against the Soviet “package”
                        proposal and would vote for the Peruvian resolution.</p>
                    <p>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SARASINP1">Sarasin</persName>, who is the Thai
                        representation on the <hi rend="italic">Ad Hoc</hi> Committee, said that he
                        was not planning to speak on this question.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>